Privacy Policy for Haunted House
Last updated: 02/09/2024
Introduction
Welcome to "Haunted House," an application provided by Software Illusions. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your personal information when you use our app. By using Haunted House, you agree to the practices described in this policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the app.
1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information:
Personal Information:
Haunted House does not directly collect any personal information (such as name, email, or phone number) unless you choose to provide it, for example, by contacting us via customer support.
If you wish to participate in the Global Highscores, your nickname and score will be stored on our servers.
Non-Personal Information:
We collect non-identifiable information related to app usage, including but not limited to device information (e.g., device type, OS version), session activity, and interaction data. This data helps us enhance app functionality and user experience.
Location Data (Optional):
If enabled, Haunted House may collect anonymous location data to provide location-based content or features. You will have the option to allow or deny location services at any time through your device settings.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information to:
Improve and personalize app functionality and performance
Analyze app usage and trends to improve content and features
Respond to customer support inquiries
3. Advertisements
Our app may display advertisements provided by third-party advertising networks. These networks may collect certain information to deliver targeted advertisements that are relevant to you. This information may include:
Device information (e.g., device ID, OS version)
Location data, if enabled
App interaction data
Third-party advertisers may use cookies, web beacons, or other technologies to collect this information. You can opt out of personalized ads by adjusting your device settings or by following the instructions provided by the advertising network.
4. Information Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may share certain information in the following cases:
Service Providers:
We may work with third-party providers who help us operate our app. These providers only receive the information needed to perform their services and are bound by confidentiality agreements.
Legal Requirements:
We may disclose information if required to do so by law or if we believe such action is necessary to comply with legal processes, protect our rights, or ensure user safety.
5. Data Security
We implement reasonable security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, disclosure, or loss. However, please be aware that no security measure is completely infallible, and we cannot guarantee absolute data security.
6. Your Choices
Opt-Out:
You may limit or prevent certain data collection by adjusting your device’s privacy settings, such as disabling location services for the app.
Access and Correction:
If we collect any personal information, you may request access or corrections by contacting us via out website, https://www.software-illusions.com.
7. Children’s Privacy
Haunted House is not intended for children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that a child under 13 has provided personal information, we will delete it in compliance with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA).
8. GDPR Compliance
If you are a resident of the European Economic Area (EEA), you have specific rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). These rights include:
Access:
You have the right to request access to your personal data that we hold, as well as information on how it is being used.
Rectification:
You have the right to request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete personal information we hold about you.
Erasure:
You have the right to request that we delete your personal data under certain conditions, such as when it is no longer necessary for the purposes for which it was collected.
Restriction of Processing:
You have the right to request a limitation on how your personal data is processed.
Data Portability:
You have the right to request a copy of your data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format.
Object to Processing:
You have the right to object to certain types of processing, such as direct marketing or profiling based on your personal data.
To exercise these rights, please contact us via our website https://www.software-illusions.com We will respond to your request in compliance with GDPR requirements.
Additionally, if you believe that our handling of your personal data is not in compliance with GDPR, you have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority in the EEA.
9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the "Last updated" date will be revised. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
10. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:
Email:
[support2@software-illusions.co.uk]
11. Consent
By using the Haunted House app, you consent to this Privacy Policy.